\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 e secrets of men; O unoriginate and everlasting Light, with Whom is no variableness, neither shadow of turning: 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 Do Thou, O Immortal King, receive our supplications which we, daring because of the multitude of Thy compassions, offer Thee at the present tim\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 
e from defiled lips; and forgive us our sins, in deed, word, and thought, whether committed by us knowingly or in ignorance, and cleanse us from every defilement of flesh and spirit. 
