test save all. 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 And again, O Saviour, save me by Thy grace, I pray Thee. For if Thou shouldst save me for my works, this would not be grace or a gift, but rather a duty; yea, Thou Who art great in compassion and ineffable in mercy. 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 For he that believeth i\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 
n Me, Thou hast said, O my Christ, shall live and never see death. If, then, faith in Thee saveth the desperate, behold, I believe, save me, for Thou art my God and Creator. 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 Let faith instead of works be imputed to me, O my God, for Thou wilt find no work\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 
s which could justify me. But may my faith suffice instead of all works, may it answer for, may it acquit me, may it make me a partaker of Thine eternal glory. 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 And let Satan not seize me and boast, O Word, that he hath torn me from Thy hand and fold. But \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 
whether I desire it or not, save me, O Christ my Saviour, forestall me quickly, quickly, for I perish. 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 Thou art my God from my mother's womb. Vouchsafe me, O Lord, to love Thee now as fervently as I once loved sin itself, and also to work for Thee without\hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 
 idleness, diligently, as I worked before for deceptive Satan. 
\par \hich\af37\dbch\af37\loch\f37 But supremely shall I work for Thee, my Lord and God, Jesus Christ, all the days of my life, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.
